Program: Outlook
Title: US Family's Shipwreck
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01dsyrg
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 15 Aug 2013
The Silverwood family describe how their dream family sailing holiday turned into a nightmare when their boat hit a remote reef in the Pacific and they were shipwrecked. Assistant professor, Maisah Sobaihi talks about becoming the first Saudi ever to perform comedy at the Edinburgh Fringe Festival. And, one man explains how good food helped him to rediscover his enjoyment of life, after losing almost everything. Show less